[[File:380kV_Forth_Crossing_-_Northern_Pylon_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1717269.jpg|thumb|North Tower]] The '''275 kV Forth Crossing''' has the tallest electricity towers (pylon<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gorge.org/pylons/envision/ |title=Pylons around the UK |publisher=The Gorge |date=2008-08-05 |accessdate=2016-02-16}}</ref> )in [[Scotland]]. They stand next to the [[Clackmannanshire Bridge]] and the [[Kincardine Bridge]], and cross the [[River Forth]]. The tower at the southern end is 153.9 metres (505&nbsp;ft),<ref>{{cite web|title=400 kV Forth Crossing, Tower South|url=http://www.emporis.com/building/400-kv-forth-crossing-tower-south-airth-united-kingdom|publisher=[[Emporis]]|accessdate=23 December 2014}}</ref> that at the northern end 137.16 metres (450&nbsp;ft) tall.<ref>{{cite web|title=400 kV Forth Crossing, Tower North|url=http://www.emporis.com/building/400-kv-forth-crossing-tower-north-kincardine-united-kingdom|publisher=Emporis|accessdate=23 December 2014}}</ref> [[File:380kV Forth Crossing - geograph.org.uk - 1717154.jpg|thumb|173px|Southern Tower]]
