==Electricity== ===Renewable energy=== The twelve newer EU Member States in Central and Eastern Europe plan to increase wind power capacity from the 6.4 gigawatts installed at the end of 2012 to 16 gigawatts by 2020.<ref>[http://www.ewea.org/press-releases/detail/?tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=2022&cHash=8038d5b6fd3f880c51b099ae3f4e5f54 Wind power for 9 million households in Eastern Europe by 2020] 5 Feb 2013</ref><ref>[http://www.ewea.org/fileadmin/files/library/publications/reports/Eastern_Winds_emerging_markets.pdf Eastern winds, Emerging European wind power markets] February 2013</ref>
If renewable electricity production in the EU continued to grow at the same rate as it did from 2005 to 2010, it would account for 36.4% of electricity in 2020 and 51.6% in 2030, following:<ref>[http://www.ewea.org/index.php?id=60&no_cache=1&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=1928&tx_ttnews%5BbackPid%5D=259&cHash=5b6ef5175da4b4475793f542a20f3a80 EU met its 2010 Renewable electricity target - ambitious 2030 target needed] EWEA 12 January 2012</ref>
