[[Image:Lacus-oblivionis-clem1.jpg|thumb|right|300px|[[Clementine (spacecraft)|Clementine]] mosaic]]
[[Image:Lacus Oblivionis AS17-151-23192-93.jpg|thumb|left|400px|Mosaic from two [[Apollo 17]] images, facing southeast]]
'''Lacus Oblivionis''' ([[Latin]] for "Lake of Forgetfulness") is a small [[lunar mare]] on the surface of the [[Moon]]. It is located at 21.0° S, 168.0° W and is 50&nbsp;km in diameter.  The name was adopted by the IAU in 1976.<ref>[http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/3213 Lacus Oblivionis], Feature 3213, Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature, International Astronomical Union (IAU) Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature (WGPSN)</ref>

The crater Mohorovičić R (satellite of [[Mohorovičić (crater)|Mohorovičić]]) lies to the northeast, and the crater Sniadecki Y (satellite of [[Sniadecki (crater)|Sniadecki]]) lies to the southwest.

