{{notability|Neologisms|date=August 2018}}
'''Offshore Transmission Owners (OFTOs)''' operate and maintain electrical transmission assets.  In some cases, they also design and build these assets. In other cases, Generators design and build the electrical transmission assets and then transfer them to OFTOs at construction completion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/electricity/transmission-networks/offshore-transmission|title=Offshore transmission|website=www.ofgem.gov.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.practicallaw.thomsonreuters.com/w-001-5923?transitionType=Default&contextData=(sc.Default)&firstPage=true&comp=pluk&bhcp=1|title=Practical Law UK Signon|website=uk.practicallaw.thomsonreuters.com}}</ref>

